.TH Q3N 1 "2026-06-25" "1.0" "Q3N Manual"

.SH NAME
q3n \- Quote Triple-Slash Notation CLI — manage quoted text collections

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B q3n
.I command
.RI [ options ] " [" args ]
.br
.B q3n
\-\-help
.br
.B q3n help
.br
.B q3n tutorial

.SH DESCRIPTION
Q3N (Quote Triple-Slash Notation) is a plain-text file format for storing
quotations, citations, and annotated excerpts with their source URIs.
Entries are delimited by \fB///\fR (open) and \fB\\\\\fR (close).

A Q3N entry looks like this in its source form:

.RS
.nf
/// https://example.com/article /// cite/article:
Quoted text goes here.
It can span multiple paragraphs.
\\\\\
.RE

.PP
.B q3n
is the command-line tool for creating, viewing, searching, and managing
Q3N files.

.SH COMMANDS

.SS show
Display entries from a Q3N file.

.B Usage:
.RS
q3n show <file> [n] [--json]
.RE

With an optional entry number, shows only that entry along with its
raw Q3N source. With \fB--json\fR, outputs structured JSON.

.SS list (ls)
Scan a directory and list all entries found across Q3N files.

.B Usage:
.RS
q3n list [directory] [--json]
.RE

.SS create
Interactive wizard for creating a new Q3N entry.
Walks through source-type selection, URI entry, tagging, and quote text.

.B Usage:
.RS
q3n create <file>
.RE

If the file exists, the new entry is appended. Otherwise a new file is
created.

.SS edit
Edit an existing entry interactively. Prompts for URI, tag, and quote
text, showing the current values as defaults.

.B Usage:
.RS
q3n edit <file> [n]
.RE

Without an entry number, lists all entries and prompts for selection.

.SS search
Search entry text using a regular expression pattern.
Matches are shown with surrounding context and highlighted.

.B Usage:
.RS
q3n search <pattern> [file-or-directory]
.RE

.SS stats
Show collection statistics: entry count, character/word counts,
tag distribution (with bar chart), and domain distribution.

.B Usage:
.RS
q3n stats [file-or-directory] [--json]
.RE

.SS export
Export entries to an alternative format.

.B Usage:
.RS
q3n export <file> -o <output> -f <format>
.RE

Supported formats: \fBtxt\fR (plain text), \fBjson\fR (structured data),
\fBmd\fR (Markdown with blockquotes), \fBq3n\fR (canonical Q3N).

.SS import
Import entries from another file (Q3N or JSON) into a Q3N file.
If the destination is a directory, a new file is created.

.B Usage:
.RS
q3n import <source> <destination> [-f q3n|json]
.RE

.SS index
Generate a markdown index of all entries showing a table with
entry numbers, URIs, tags, and previews, grouped by tag.

.B Usage:
.RS
q3n index [file-or-directory]
.RE

.SS init
Create a new empty Q3N file with the \fB#!q3n-format\fR header.

.B Usage:
.RS
q3n init <file>
.RE

.SS tutorial
Display an interactive tutorial introducing the Q3N format and CLI commands.

.B Usage:
.RS
q3n tutorial
.RE

.SS help
Show this man page or detailed help for any command.

.B Usage:
.RS
q3n help [command]
.RE

.SH FILE FORMAT

.B Q3N
uses the following structure:

.RS
.nf
#!q3n-format

/// <source_uri> [/// <tag>:]
<quoted text, possibly multi-line>
\\\\\
.RE

.TP
.B #!q3n-format
Optional header for file-type identification.
.TP
.B /// <uri> [/// <tag>:]
Opening delimiter, source URI, and optional tag. The URI is any valid
scheme-prefixed identifier (https://, file://, isbn://, doi://, etc.).
Tags use a slash for hierarchy (e.g., \fBcite/article\fR, \fBnote/idea\fR)
and are terminated by a colon.
.TP
.B <quoted text>
The content — any UTF-8 text, multiple lines.
.TP
.B \\\\
Closing delimiter (three backslashes) on its own line.

.SS URI Schemes

.TP
.B https:// http://
Web page URLs.
.TP
.B file://
Local file paths; append \fB#line=N\fR for line references.
.TP
.B isbn://
Book references; format: \fBisbn://ISBN;'Title';'Author';Year\fR.
.TP
.B doi://
Academic paper DOIs.
.TP
.B arxiv://
arXiv preprint IDs.
.TP
.B yt://
YouTube video identifiers.
.TP
.B q3n://
Person references; format: \fBq3n://@handle;email;'Name'\fR.

.SH EXAMPLES

Create your first Q3N collection:
.RS
$ q3n init my-quotes.q3n
$ q3n create my-quotes.q3n
.RE

List entries and show one in detail:
.RS
$ q3n list .
$ q3n show my-quotes.q3n 1
.RE

Export as Markdown:
.RS
$ q3n export my-quotes.q3n -o quotes.md -f md
.RE

Search across all files:
.RS
$ q3n search "Stonewall" .
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT

No environment variables are required. The tool auto-detects color
support based on whether stdout is a terminal. Pass \fB--no-color\fR
to disable ANSI escape sequences.

.SH FILES

Q3N files conventionally use the extension \fB.q3n\fR.
Alternative extensions: \fB.q3nt\fR, \fB.quotation\fR, \fB.quotes\fR.

